-- Nigeria to Borrow $300 Million for Water Projects, This Day Says
-- B y   M a r a m   M a z e n
-- 2012-11-06T11:20:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-06/nigeria-to-borrow-300-million-for-water-projects-this-day-says.html
Nigeria plans to borrow $300 million
for water supply projects in the West African nation, Finance
Minister Ngozi Okonjo-Iweala told lawmakers, according to
ThisDay newspaper.  The proposal is part of an initial request for $7.9 billion
that has been pending before Parliament and $1.4 billion more
including the water request for works in several states, the
paper said, citing the borrowing plan unveiled before
legislators yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Maram Mazen in Abuja at 
 mmazen@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Randall Hackley at 
 rhackley@bloomberg.net  